newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 1156 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 1156 contracts.

text.p: The Chicago Board of Trade Project A overnight agricultural contracts trading volume totalled 1,156 contracts, compared with 730 contracts traded overnight on Sunday, according to the CBOT.
There were 142 wheat, 314 corn, 663 soybean, 28 soymeal and nine soyoil futures contracts traded along with three soybean call, nine soybean put and 10 corn put options.

In overnight trading, wheat was 1/2 cent lower to one cent per bushel higher, soybeans down 1-1/2 to 2-1/4 cents lower, corn down 1/4 cent, soymeal down 50 cents per ton, and soyoil down 0.01 cent per lb.
